==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|No, it wasn't a myth, and the issue is still there with using the name 'Sunrider.'&thinsp;|[[Sue Rostoni]], Executive Editor of [[Lucas Licensing]]|<ref name="sue" />}}
From [[1993]] to [[1998]], [[Dark Horse Comics]] published [[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi (comic series)|''Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi'']], a [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series composed of eight story arcs. Five of the eight arcs featured the characters [[Nomi Sunrider|Nomi]] and [[Vima Sunrider]], a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] and her young daughter. Nomi was a principal character in four arcs, while Vima took center stage as a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] apprentice in 1998's [[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Redemption|''Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi - Redemption'']].<ref name="totj1">''[[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – The Saga of Nomi Sunrider]]''</ref><ref name="totj2">''[[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – The Freedon Nadd Uprising]]''</ref><ref name="TOTJ3">''[[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith]]''</ref><ref name="TOTJ4">''[[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War]]''</ref><ref name="totj5">[[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Redemption|''Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi - Redemption'']]</ref> Nomi's [[Marriage/Legends|husband]] [[Andur Sunrider]] briefly appeared in 1993's ''[[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – The Saga of Nomi Sunrider]]'',<ref name="totj3" /><ref name="totj4">[[Tales of the Jedi 4|''Tales of the Jedi'' 4]]</ref> and his grandfather [[Jev Sunrider]] was mentioned in the [[1996]] sourcebook ''[[Tales of the Jedi Companion]]''.<ref name="TOTJC" /> These members of the Sunrider family were referenced in several other works of ''[[Star Wars]]'' media published throughout the 1990s.<ref name="de2">''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire II]]''</ref><ref name="da">[[Dark Apprentice (novel)|''Dark Apprentice'']]</ref><ref name="jjk">''[[Junior Jedi Knights: Vader's Fortress]]''</ref>

At some point in time, legal issues began to arise over [[Lucasfilm]]'s use of the name "Sunrider."<ref name="avellone">{{WebCite|url=http://forums.obsidian.net/topic/30458-so-where-is-vima-sunrider-during-the-kotor-story/#entry281372|text=So where is Vima Sunrider during the Kotor story?|author=Chris Avellone|date=23-02-2005|work=Obsidian Forum Community|archivedate=20160801011745}}</ref><ref name="sue">{{SWBoards|url=message.jspa?messageID=17382195#17382195|thread=Thread: Books, Comics, & Television VIPs|user=[[Sue Rostoni]]|date=2008-09-30|time=9:12 AM}}</ref> It remains unclear to the public who the offended party was, but fans have speculated that a lawsuit was filed by the [[Wikipedia:Jeep|Jeep]] Corporation,<ref name="spec">{{JCFCite|url=posts/23786816|board=Literature|thread=What KOTOR characters would you like to see in &hellip;. KOTOR?|user=Leto II|date=2006-05-01|time=10:27 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801161518/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/what-kotor-characters-would-you-like-to-see-in-kotor.23779273}}.</ref><ref name="broox">{{SWBoards|url=message.jspa?messageID=17382153#17382153|thread=Untitled Nomi Sunrider Novel by Alex Irvine *Speculation*|user=The Broox|date=2008-09-30|time=8:36 AM}}</ref> who manufacture a [[Wikipedia:Trademark|trademarked]] jeep soft top called "Sunrider."<ref name="jeepsite">{{WebCite|url=http://www.jeepsandstuff.com/jeep---76-95-cj-7---wrangler-tops--sunrider-.html|text=Sunrider™ Jeep Tops|work=jeepsandstuff.com|archivedate=20080608223539}}</ref> However, this rumor has not been verified by any Lucasfilm employees, and has additionally been contested by ''Star Wars'' author [[Kyle Jewhurst]]. According to Jewhurst, Dark Horse Vice President of Publishing [[Randy Stradley]] has reported that the legal issues arose from ''Tales of the Jedi'' author [[Tom Veitch]] having used the name "Sunrider" in another work.<ref name="Hydro">{{JCFCite|url=posts/29178189|board=Literature|thread="Mandorla" &ndash; Alex Irvine TOTJ/KOTOR/Nomi Sunrider 2011 Hardcover|user=[[Kyle Jewhurst|Lord Hydronium]]|date=2008-09-19|time=8:41 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116070949/http://boards.theforce.net/threads/mandorla-alex-irvine-totj-kotor-nomi-sunrider-2011-hardcover.29177883}}</ref>

[[File:Vimaart.jpg|thumb|right|150px|''Knights of the Old Republic'' concept art of Vima Sunrider]]
When the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'' was in development, Vima Sunrider was slated to be one of its protagonists, but the legal issues prompted the development team to instead create a new character named [[Bastila Shan]].<ref name="avellone" /><ref name="db">{{DB|character|bastilashan|Shan, Bastila}}</ref> The game is set [[3956 BBY|thirty years]] after the final story arc of ''Tales of the Jedi'' and references Nomi several times, but only once by her last name.<ref name="kotor">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref> That instance was an oversight by the development team. They were also forbidden from using the name in the game's [[2004]] sequel, ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''.<ref name="avellone" />

Presently, the legal issues continue to exist, but do not preclude the appearance of a Sunrider within ''Star Wars'' media, nor the use of the family name. The latter is permissible within the body of a text where it cannot be confused with any other trademarked product, but cannot be used in a book's title nor be attached to an action figure.<ref name="sue" /> Nomi has been mentioned by her full name in several novels and sourcebooks published since ''Knights of the Old Republic'',<ref name="cn1">''[[Coruscant Nights I: Jedi Twilight]]''</ref><ref name="nec">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref><ref name="jvs">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref> although ''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]'', an [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|MMORPG]] released in [[2011]], refers to her as "Nomi-Da-Boda" and refers to both Vima and Andur only by their first names.<ref name="The Old Republic">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]'', Consular storyline</ref> Both Nomi and Vima<ref name="Vima too">{{Blogspot|subdomain=yetistomper|url=2009/09/keeping-eye-on-alex-irvine.html|name=Stomping on Yeti|text=Keeping An Eye On&hellip; Alex Irvine}}</ref> were originally set to star in a [[2012]] [[Mandorla|novel]],<ref name="new mandorla date">{{SWBoards|url=message.jspa?messageID=17950706#17950706|thread=The Expanded Universe VIPs 3.0|user=[[Sue Rostoni]]|date=2011-01-28|time=12:13 PM}}</ref> but the book was eventually canceled, reportedly due to "changes in direction and concepts in the overall publishing plans."<ref name="cancelled">{{Facebook|username=starwarsbooks|url=starwarsbooks/posts/10150654342868713|name=Star Wars Books|date=2012-02-29|archivedate=20200525012235}}</ref>

